, 
<figureCitation id="137C21F5FFDBFFA6DC1720A9C837FA4F" box="[513,542,1438,1463]" captionStart="FIGURE 34" captionStartId="55.[151,250,1939,1961]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,451,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-149@55.[151,1437,447,1917]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURE 34. Leucophenga platypyga Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia in lateral view. A. Epandrium, surstylus, and cercus; B. Hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus, and aedeagal apodeme; C. Paramere; D. Aedeagus. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297956" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297956/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">34</figureCitation>
